<p class="title">Code examples, from lecture and otherwise</p>

<p>Over the course of the quarter, as we work on code in lecture, I'll be providing commented code examples for you.  These examples are mostly to give you clean and well-documented examples of some of the things we cover in lecture (and possibly a few things that we don't, time permitting), so that you can be free in lecture to avoid trying to take detailed notes when we're writing code together, instead concentrating on understanding the process and the bigger-picture concepts at work when we develop the examples.</p>

